{"id":"grate","term":"Grate","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A network of brass for the bottom of the great altar of sacrifice (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 27:4\">Ex. 27:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 35:16\">35:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 38:4\">38:4</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 38:5\">5</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 38:30\">30</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 27:4","Exodus 35:16","Exodus 38:4","Exodus 38:5","Exodus 38:30"]}